Two people were killed and two others injured on Monday by elephants in Meru and Tharaka-Nithi counties.The four elephants strayed from the Meru National Park Sunday night, officials said.In Tharaka a seventeen-year-old boy from Igumo village was killed while in Meru County a man from Nthambiro village was killed.A woman from Tharaka who was injured by the furious elephants is receiving treatment at Tharaka Sub-County Hospital.Meru National Park Senior Warden Tuqa Jirmo told the Nation on phone that Kenya Wild Life Service (KWS) rangers shot dead one of the elephants.